Name: vaccination control measure
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: A control measure in which individuals in a population are vaccinated

Name: ascertainment fraction
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: Fraction of all symptomatic individuals who will be ascertained

Name: antiviral course
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: The quantity of antiviral drug used to treat one individual

Name: vaccine valence
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: the number of distinct antigenic strains in a vaccine product

Name: control measure compliance
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: the fraction of a individuals who receive or participate in an offered control measure

Name: Reactive control measure test
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: An event in the simulated population that triggers the start of a reactive control measure

Name: reactive control measure threshold
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: Fraction of the population ascertained as having disease that results in initiating a reactive control measure

Name: simulating of process of type X
Definition: a planned process that (1) has at least one process part that has as participants representations of participants (in place of those participants) of processes of type X, and where all such process parts substitute for parts of processes of type X, and (2) is carried out for the purpose of planning for processes of type X, learning more about processes of type X, or teaching about processes of type X.
Elucidation: the process of simulating a process of type X.  This term is not used in Apollo-WS.

Name: epidemic simulation
Definition: A simulating of a disease epidemic or pandemic.
Elucidation: the process of simulating a disease epidemic or pandemic. This term is not currently used in Apollo-WS.

Name: control measure
Definition: A process that is applied to a population with the goal of preventing, or mitigating the severity of a disease.
Elucidation: Elucidation not defined in ontology

Name: time step unit
Definition: The time unit that is part of a simulation time step action specification.
Elucidation: The time unit such as "hours" or "days" for each time step of a simulation.  Time step unit is always used with time step value.

Name: simulation time step action specification
Definition: An action specification that specifies the length of the time steps interval assumed in a simulation.
Elucidation: Elucidation not defined in ontology

Name: run length
Definition: The action specification that specifies the number of time steps a simulation is going to run.
Elucidation: The number of time steps for a simulator run.  If run length is 10 and time step is 6 hours, then the simulator will simulate a 60-hour period.

Name: vaccination dose schedule
Definition: An action specification comprising the number of doses and their timing for a vaccination of an individual organism against a specific infectious agent.
Elucidation: A vaccination schedule specifies the intended timing of initial and subsequent booster doses of vaccine for an individual organism.

Name: antiviral supply schedule
Definition: An objective specification giving the number of doses of an antiviral to be made available during a specific time interval.
Elucidation: Counts of antiviral doses that become available in a specific location per time step unit.

Name: antiviral administration schedule
Definition: An objective specification giving the number of antiviral doses possible in a population during a specific time interval.
Elucidation: Counts of antiviral doses that can be administered in a specific location per time step unit.

Name: vaccine supply schedule
Definition: An objective specification giving the number of doses of vaccine to be made available over a specific time period.
Elucidation: The counts of vaccine doses that become available in a specific population location during (at the start of would be unambiguous) each simulator time step.

Name: epidemic control objective specification
Definition: An objective specification that is realized by processes that are able or likely to stop the spread of a disease in a population.
Elucidation: Elucidation not defined in ontology

Name: vaccination administration capacity
Definition: An objective specification giving the number of vaccinations possible in a population during a specific time interval.
Elucidation: The counts of individuals that could be vaccinated in a population location per time step unit in the absence of any vaccine supply constraints.  It represents the capacity of medical system to vaccinate individuals.

Name: time series
Definition: A time sampled measurement data set, where the position in the sequence of each data item corresponds to a specific time_step of the simulation.
Elucidation: A sequence of data points, where the position in the sequence of each data point corresponds to a specific time_step of the simulation.

Name: reproduction number
Definition: The average value of transmissions of the infectious agent from one infected organism to another, resulting in an infection.
Elucidation: The number of susceptible organisms that each infected organism infects.  'Infects' carries the same meaning as 'exposes' in epidemic simulations such as SEIR simulation.

Name: antiviral efficacy delay
Definition: The value of the time interval between an organism's taking antivirals against a specific infectious agent and the organism's losing its infectious agent host role.
Elucidation: The duration of time (expressed in time steps) between initiation of a particular antiviral treatment to an organism and when the organism becomes non infectious or, if the antiviral is being administered prophylactically, protected from infection.

Name: latent period
Definition: The measurement datum of the time interval between the host's extended organism acquiring an infection as a part and the host bearing a contagiousness disposition in the curse of the same disease course within a population of hosts.
Elucidation: The duration of the period between when an organism becomes infected and when it becomes infectious.

Name: infectious period
Definition: The measurement datum for the duration of the parts of an infectious disease course during which the host bears an infectious disposition in a population of hosts.
Elucidation: The duration of the infectiousness of infectious individuals in a population expressed in time step units, for example "6.1"

Name: antiviral cm compliance
Definition: The fraction expressing the probability that an organism will be consented to receiving antiviral treatment when eligible.
Elucidation: The fraction of individuals in a simulated population that will accept antiviral treatment if offered.

Name: asymptomatic infection fraction
Definition: The fraction given to express the probability of an organism to be infected, but stay asymptomatic.
Elucidation: The fraction of infectious individuals who do not develop symptoms during the course of their infections.

Name: vaccination efficacy
Definition: The fraction expressing the probability of an organism who has been administered a vaccine to acquire immunity.
Elucidation: The fraction of vaccinated organisms in a simulated population that acquire immunity due to the vaccination.

Name: vaccination cm compliance
Definition: The fraction expressing the probability of an organism who is eligible according to a particular vaccination policy to be consented for that vaccination.
Elucidation: The fraction of individuals in a population who are eligible according to a particular vaccination policy and will accept vaccination assuming no supply constraint.

Name: antiviral efficacy
Definition: The fraction expressing the probability of an organism who has been administered an antiviral to stop being an infectious agent host.
Elucidation: The fraction of a specific simulated population that receives antiviral treatment against a specific virus that either loses its infectious agent host role due to the antiviral treatment or does not become infected if the antiviral agent is being administered prophylactically (e.g., to household contacts of infected individuals).

Name: count of simulated exposed population
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: Elucidation not defined in ontology

Name: count of simulated susceptible population
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: Elucidation not defined in ontology

Name: count of simulated resistant population
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: Elucidation not defined in ontology

Name: pop_count
Definition: The count of (simulated organisms) in a simulated population.
Elucidation: The number of simulated organisms in a simulated population.  The number does not have to be an integer.

Name: count of simulated contagious population
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: Elucidation not defined in ontology

Name: run id
Definition: A numeral that indexes a specific simulation.
Elucidation: The run id indexes a run of a specific simulator version on a specific simulated population, disease(s), and optionally control measures.  The simulator is responsible for generating a run id and ensuring its uniqueness.

Name: time step
Definition: A numeral that indexes a specific simulated time step of a simulation.
Elucidation: A numeral that indexes a specific time step of a simulation.

Name: time step value
Definition: The numeral that is part of a simulation time step action specification.
Elucidation: Time step value is the number of time step units that make up a time step in a simulation.  For example, if time step is 6 hours, then time step value is 6.

Name: software version
Definition: An information content entity that as part of a complete software identifier identifies one specific version of the software.
Elucidation: Elucidation not defined in ontology

Name: requester id
Definition: An identifier that refers to the legal person that commissions the simulation process.
Elucidation: An identifier that refers to the person or organization who is requesting one or more executions of the simulator software.

Name: complete simulator identifier
Definition: An identifier that refers to a specific simulator.
Elucidation: The combination of simulator developer, simulator name, and simulator version, for example "www.psc.edu/FRED/2.0"  The combination is intended to uniquely identify the simulation algorithm that produced output X, given input Y to support scientific audit, error analysis, and reproducibility of results.

Name: simulator developer
Definition: An identifier that refers to the legal person that creates and maintains a simulator.
Elucidation: An identifier that refers to the person or organization who is responsible for the simulator.  It is intended to uniquely identify a person or organization.  That said, we do not plan to control the namespace for simulator developer at this point in development.  We will add our ideas about alternatives at a future date.

Name: population location
Definition: An identifier that refers to a geographical location to be used as location of a population in a simulation.
Elucidation: An identifier referring to geographical location of a simulated population.  Our intent is for the location identifiers to be INCITS codes.

Name: software developer
Definition: An identifier that refers to the legal person that creates and maintains software.
Elucidation: Elucidation not defined in ontology

Name: simulator developer
Definition: An identifier that refers to the legal person that creates and maintains a simulator.
Elucidation: An identifier that refers to the person or organization who is responsible for the simulator.  It is intended to uniquely identify a person or organization.  That said, we do not plan to control the namespace for simulator developer at this point in development.  We will add our ideas about alternatives at a future date.

Name: simulator name
Definition: An identifier that refers to all version of a specific simulator.
Elucidation: An identifier that refers to all versions of a specific simulator, such as "FRED".  We intend that it uniquely identify a simulator when combined with simulator developer.  For example, the combination www.psc.edu/FRED would differentiate the FRED simulator created by a Pittsburgh organization from another "FRED" simulator maintained elsewhere. The implementation of namespace control for simulator name (i.e., making sure that they don't use "FRED" twice) is the responsibility of simulator developer.

Name: software name
Definition: An identifier that refers to all version of a specific software.
Elucidation: Elucidation not defined in ontology

Name: simulator version
Definition: An information content entity that as part of a complete simulator identifier identifies one specific version of a simulator software.
Elucidation: An identifier that refers to a unique version of a simulator. Simulator version distinguishes, for example, version "2.0" from "2.0.b"

Name: simulation
Definition: A purely intentional entity that simulates an entity and its properties.
Elucidation: Elucidation not defined in ontology

Name: exposed
Definition: A simulation of an infectious agent host that is not contagious and is part of a simulated population.
Elucidation: A simulated organism in a simulated population that has acquired a particular simulated disease but is not yet able to transmit the disease to another simulated organism.

Name: not awaiting control measure
Definition: A simulated organism that is assumed "ineligible, unwilling or unable" to participate with a particular control measure.
Elucidation: A simulated organism in a simulated population that is "ineligible, unwilling or unable" to participate with a particular simulated control measure.

Name: awaiting effect of control measure
Definition: A simulated organism that  participates in a particular control measure that has not yet been effective.
Elucidation: This concept represents a simulated organism that has received a control measure such as vaccination in which a period of time must elapse before the benefit of the control measure accrues.  A simulated organism is 'awaiting efficacy' if 'efficacy delay' (e.g. the concept 'antiviral efficacy delay' for the particular simulated control measure is greater than the elapsed time between application of the control measure and the current simulated time.

Name: disease
Definition: A representation of a disposition realized in a represented disease course that at least part of the simulated population is represented as participating in.
Elucidation: The disease being simulated.

Name: recovered
Definition: A simulated organism in a simulated population that is not susceptible.
Elucidation: A simulated organism in a simulated population that is neither susceptible, exposed, nor infectious for a particular simulated disease.  Note that the name for this concept, were it to be named based on its intent, would be 'immune.'  However, in the practice domain of epidemiology this concept is traditionally termed 'recovered.'  The problem with the traditional name is that organisms can be considered 'recovered' by virtue of having been vaccinated, which differs from lay usage.

Name: awaiting control measure
Definition: A simulated organism that is assumed "eligible, willing and able" to participate with a particular control measure.
Elucidation: A simulated organism in a simulated population that is "eligible, willing and able" to participate with a particular simulated control measure.

Name: infectious
Definition: A simulation of an infectious organism host that is contagious.
Elucidation: A simulated organism in a simulated population that has acquired a particular simulated disease and is able to transmit the disease to another simulated organism.

Name: simulation time step
Definition: A purely intentional entity that simulates a temporal interval of pre-specified length.
Elucidation: Elucidation not defined in ontology

Name: symptomatic
Definition: A simulation of a symptomatic infectious agent host.
Elucidation: A simulated organism in a simulated population that has at least one symptom caused by a particular simulated disease.

Name: susceptible organism
Definition: A simulation of a susceptible organism in a simulated population.
Elucidation: A simulated organism in a simulated population that is capable of acquiring a particular simulated disease.

Name: received control measure
Definition: A simulation of an organism in a simulated population that has participated in an epidemic control measure.
Elucidation: A simulated organism in a simulated population has participated in a particular simulated control measure. (e.g. an organism received antiviral treatment)

Name: asymptomatic
Definition: A simulation of an asymptomatic infectious agent host.
Elucidation: A simulated organism in a simulated population that has no symptoms caused by a particular simulated disease.

Name: vaccination control measure
Definition: A simulation of a vaccination control measure.
Elucidation: A type of control measure that uses vaccination to create immunity in simulated organisms to specific pathogens.

Name: anitviral control measure
Definition: The simulation of an antiviral control measure.
Elucidation: A type of control measure based on administration of chemotherapeutic agents to an infected or high-risk organism that kill or inhibit replication of viruses within a simulated organism.

Name: simulated population location
Definition: The simulation of geographical location in which a  population is assumed to be located.
Elucidation: An identifier referring to geographical location of a simulated population.  Our intent is for the location identifiers to be INCITS codes.

Name: simulated population
Definition: A simulation of the aggregate of organisms that are members of the population participating in a simulator.
Elucidation: A simulated population is a set of simulated organisms.  The set can be null (e.g., the set of 200 year-old H. sapiens).  A simulated population can include more than one species, in which case it may be convenient to define each species as a simulated population and form the overall simulated population by set union.  Similarly, it may be convenient to define sociodemographic or geographic strata within a simulated population as simulated populations and obtain the overall simulated population by set union.  See examples in "Programmer's Guide, page x)

Name: disease organism
Definition: An organism that has an infectious disposition.
Elucidation: an organism that causes infection

Name: host organism
Definition: An organism bearing a host role.
Elucidation: an organism that is the subject of infection

Name: population
Definition: An object aggregate of organisms.
Elucidation: This term refers to a real population, such as the population of Allegheny County or of the U.S.   As a set, it could null (size zero), for example the population of people in Allegheny County older than 130 years of age.  It could also be a single organism. The population is not restricted to members of one species.

Name: vaccination reactive end point fraction
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: a fraction of vaccination of individuals in a target population at which a vaccination program stops vaccinating that target population

Name: control measure start time
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: The time step during which a control measure begins

Name: control measure response delay
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: Number of time steps delay between a decision to start a control measure and initiation of control measure.

Name: vaccine efficacy delay
Definition: The time measurement datum of the time interval between the beginning of a vaccination against an infectious agent and the participant's acquisition of immunity.
Elucidation: The duration of the time period between an organism's participation in a vaccination against a specific infectious agent and the organism's acquisition of immunity against that infectious agent.

Name: geophysical geographical location data set
Definition: A data set containing geophysical information about a geographical region.
Elucidation: A data set containing geophysical information about a geographical region. This term is not currently used in Apollo-WS.

Name: control measure name
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: Elucidation not defined in ontology

Name: ascertainment delay
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: Number of time steps it takes medical personnel to ascertain a symptomatic individual from onset of symptoms

Name: control measure target population and prioritization
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: A simulated population that is the target of a control measure and its priority under triage conditions

Name: control measure target facilities
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: Faciilities that are the target of a control measure

Name: school calendar
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: The time steps that a school will be in session.

Name: school closure duration
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: The number of time steps that a school closure control measure prescribes that schools will remain closed.

Name: susceptibility
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: A number between 0 and 1 indicating the degree of susceptibility of an organism

Name: random number seed
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: random number seed

Name: inter-personal contact probability
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: Transmission parameter

Name: Reactive control measure
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: a control measure (program) that is initiated or modified by an epidemic-related event (or if you prefer, an event occurring within/during the simulation)

Name: beta
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: Transmission parameter (sometime known as Ptrans). This value is multiplied by the inter-personal contact probability to determine the transmission probability between infected and susceptible persons.

Name: control measure target population fraction
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: Fraction of organisms in a target population that a control measure program seeks to enroll or prioritize

Name: antiviral ID
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: A unique identifier for an antiviral drug

Name: school closure control measure
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: A control measure in which schools are closed in an attempt to reduce transmission of disease

Name: vaccination course
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: the number of doses of vaccine that are recommended to achieve immunity

Name: species
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: an interbreeding population

Name: vaccination ID
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: A unique identifier for a vaccination protocol (the process of vaccinating one person)

Name: vaccine ID
Definition: Definition not defined in ontology
Elucidation: A unique identifier for a vaccine
